<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-30T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-30T11:00:00-05:00" n="660" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d660">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857Ar5/2</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-30T16:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1915, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.30 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2378. Consul at Bristol reports that British authorities state <hi rend="italic">Armenian</hi> of Leyland Line from Newport News to
                                British port has been torpedoed and sunk by German submarine <hi rend="italic">U–38</hi> off Cornwall. Consul reports twenty-one
                                Americans lost. British Admiralty informs me that ship was engaged
                                on Admiralty business and understands she carried no passengers.
                                Americans lost therefore appear to be members of crew.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>